The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, April 4: Arindam Haldar, a stockbroker, was kidnapped outside his office near City Centre in Salt Lake this afternoon and rescued from a house in Muchipara late in the night. 

 A resident of Survey Park in Jadavpur, Haldar had borrowed Rs 6 lakh from different people, out of which he had paid back only Rs 3.5 lakh. Police are probing if his creditors had anything to do with the four kidnappers.

 Calcutta: A private tutor has been arrested in South 24-Parganas Kakdwip for allegedly killing a nine-year-old student. Superintendent of police S.N. Gupta said Pintu Chakraborty had been asking Biswajit haldars father to close down his liquor shop at Kakdwip bazar as he felt it vitiated the atmosphere there. Swapan did not pay heed to it. 

 Calcutta: The CID filed an affidavit in the high court on Wednesday admitting that a preliminary probe had revealed that Congress supporter Tushar Samanta was killed by a bullet fired by the then Katwa officer-in-charge in February. The CID said a mob provoked the OC after a school poll turned violent.

 Krishnagar: BSF jawans were accused of tonsuring two men in their in their 30s and blackening their face with paint after suspecting them to be smugglers. Khaser Mondal and Laltu Biswas, who were cycling, were stopped near the Chapra border in Nadia.




